Probably one of the reasons people feel like shit whenever they sleep too long, like 9-10 hours, is blood sugar crashing, unable to regulate itself for so long without eating, thus breaking the continuous single sleep block by taking a longer afternoon nap seems like a good idea.

If drinking sugared milk, salty snacks to lower adrenalin before bed, etc. adjusts sleep quality at the front of sleep, then cutting the total time of nighttime sleep for an extra siesta is just doing the same for the other end by externalizing it... My grandpa and dad love naps.

All Hellenic texts were written specifically with old English classics and philology professors in mind, who wear suits and attend archaeological excavations in the summer. This is the true target audience. Also German businessmen merchants and early Romantic poets (also anglo).

Truly one of our fellow intellectual titans' sharpest insights. Other genius musings include: "You are not a 12th century BC Greek warrior.", "You are not Japanese novelist Yukio Mishima.", and even "The spoon object disappears when it is no longer in my direct field of vision."

The masses are to Rene Guenon merely the subconscious memory of mankind. Thus dying traditions' last representatives often divulge their inner stories to the folk to preserve them. This is a "lunar" function, thus folklore says everything lost on earth can be found on the moon.

I guess the "romanticization" of the peasantry today is precisely due to this moon-like reflection of sunlight now missing its true source, the virtues properly belonging to the aristocracy, free citizenry, etc. can only be found as fainter remnants in "natural" rural households.
